  p Recap: From around 11 or 12 months of age, humans spontaneously use pointing to ...
    ul
      li request
      li inform
      li initiate joint engagement (‘Wow! That!’)
  .notes Why is this significant?
  .notes Because it implies two things:
  .notes First, it implies that infants' pointing is referential communication; that is, communication about an object.
  .notes (Contrast sharing a smile; we're communicating, but not necessarily referring.)
  .notes Second, it implies that infants have some understanding of joint engagement.

